Loading external javascript file in index.html of React App

I have this React app in which I load my external javascript file inside the tag as below index.html:
```
....
<script type="text/javascript" src="../src/assets/externalJavascript.js"></script>
</head>
```

Inside externalJavascript.js, I have this below:
```
let queryParams = window.location.search.substring(1);

console.log("Query: ", queryParams)

window.loadFunc = function loadFunc() {
            console.log("Script Loaded!");
          };
```

I access this loadFunc() inside my desired component using window.loadFunc()

All this is not working but if I make the js file inline in the index.html, it's working! Like this below:
```
<script>
      (function () {
          let queryParams = window.location.search.substring(1);

          console.log("Query: ", queryParams);

          window.loadFunc = function loadFunc() {
            console.log("Script Loaded!");
          };
      })()
    </script>
```

When my app loads, I get the query in console log and also I can access the loadFunc() only when it is inline script.

Please help me to solve this.

Thank you!

